,Recommended,295590,15330007,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,Kuehnau,"Alright, so I just got this game.. And I like it, I think it's a lot of fun, it's sort of like a lite Roguelike and a Civilization game rolled up into a bite sized game.There are issues that kind of make you feel like you aren't making progress. For starters, there's a ""world disaster"" event in the game and the count down to it is far too short, you've barely just started playing when it makes itself known.Further, any upgrades you make around other towns degrade slowly over time, even with the black smith utility. What makes this frustrating is, there's not really a point to upgrading each ""world"" unless you intend to spend any extended amount of time there. It feels like wasted resources and can be aggravating.The random element of the combat can be frustrating; it's all based on simple dice rolls. And even if you have a ability of 200 and are fighting a enemy with an ability of 30, there's still a chance they'll beat you. There's gear and buffs you can get later on, that add on bonuses to your ability and strength, which helps a lot, but early on, it's a problem.The game isn't really polished all that much either. There's been a few glitches I've run into that is really frustrating. The first is that the game is supposed to save after every move, but several times now my save files decided to just delete themselves or become something entirely different. Another issue I've been running into is, suddenly the game just won't let me move or skip any turns. The game is still running, I can open the quest menu, I just can't move.The game needs a little more polishing, there's some mechanics that could really stand to be changed and there's a few bugs to squash, but besides that, the game is fairly fun and the price tag isn't bad. Even with the issues I have had, I still can recommend it to like minded players."
