,Recommended,295590,15339074,"Posted: 13 April, 2015",all,Silva,"---Warning long review incoming---This is based only on a couple of hours in. Oh! My english is not that good, so it's possible you see some mistakes.That said, let's get into the subject. The game has an interesting concept. The mix of ""5 Minutes Civilization"" as the dev said and the ""Rogue-Like"" genre, with the mechanic of mating so you can build a legacy make the whole idea interesting. The devs wanted the game to be accessible to everyone, so the game may be a bit simplistic.What is the result?Well... they managed to do something good, but i'll be honest, it's not the indie game of the month. You start in your village, and go fight monsters, build improvements to nearby towns so when you move on these tiles you get bonus (like more Strength, more Lifespan, Gold, etc.)You get quests as you go to other worlds, and you have a main quest too. So, you have your objectives, now it is up to you to find how you are going to accomplish them.The fact that they made the game accessible to everyone makes the game way too easy for harcore gamers, or some devoted gamers in general. The casual gamer type will find some fun, or even our kids or just new gamers.I don't want to spoil anything because there isn't much to discover in the game and it will destroy ""the magic"" if I tell you everything right now. Let me do a quick Pros/Cons list, so you'll have a better idea about the game.Pros___-Beautifull art-style. Simplistic, but still nice.-Nice music. Yeah... it's good.Now the real stuff-Good mix of genres (Simplistic 4x + Rogue-Like)-Friendly game that anyone can play-Interesting RPG system with the gear limit (2) , the traits you pass down, etcNeutral----Simplistic (i think i said that word a couple times now)-Easy-The art style, depends on your tastesCons----Too easy for the more dedicated gamers (way too easy for hardcores)-Doesn't have much content (not enough gear, traits, worlds, monster types)-Feel sometimes like a pocket game you would play on a phone or tablet-A girl named Bob, a boy named Josephine... -.- Seriously Heart Shaped Games LLC please fix your name generator (sorry for all Female Bob and Male Josephine out there)-Only 1 save slot-A ""Main Menu"" button would be nice by the way-More screen resolutions needed-Fullscreen and Borderless FullScreen is missing-What is this volume setting? It's like my phone. Make a slider or something please.-Fights are ful RNG based (My hero have 40 Str, my oponent 10, I roll a 6 he roll 8, he wins the fight and hit me with 5 damage, so i lose 5 years of my life)-Somehow overpriced (here it's 16,99 CAD$ full price, so i think $14,99 USD. Maybe if it was $9,99 USD (around 11 or 12 CAD), it would be more worth the money.And there is more i'm pretty sure, but i'll stop here because the rest is my personnal opinion, and it doesn't count right now.I heard this somewhere and I can't find who said that, but it's a very good way to think about games. Each dollar spent on a game should be worth one hour of fun. So in this case, the game must give you at least 15h of good time. Well, even if I found the game to be very easy, I still think  I spent some good time on it, because it was a relaxing experience. Sometimes, easy games are fun, even for more hardcore gamers.So, overall, I still recommend this game. But keep in mind that it's a small game for the public. So don't buy it if you want intense combats, deep strategy and complexity. This is really what the devs call it. a ""5 Minutes Civilization"" with Rogue-Like elements.This was Hero Generations.My personnal rating: 7/10Worth buying at: $11.25 USD or less."
